reviews.text: This is the worse carry out ever! The food was tasteless and EXTREMELY greasy. I would never recommend this to no one even if it’s your last resort! There are better carry outs in close proximity do yourself a favor and go to one of those because this place isn’t it.

If I could give 0 I would. Very very horrible customer service. It was going to be my first time ordering here and thankfully I didn’t. He yelled at me and cussed only for asking simple questions. Horrible.
Stood there for 5 minutes saying excuse me and waiting to be serviced, only to be ignored. I’m sure the person could hear me and wow what a nasty way to treat paying customer.

The two people I see working are always very kind and speedy. Food is ready in around 10 minutes and prices are fair. I can’t speak highly enough of the staff. The building is quaint but the food and customer service make this a 5-star experience!

live in the neighborhood and decided to order lunch. very simple order, egg drop soup, two eggrolls and extra fried noodles that come with the soup and the lady on the phone who clearly misunderstood a question of “do you fry the noodles yourself or are they prepackaged” turned our conversation into an all out yelling match on the phone and in store when I came to pick up the food. avoid this location smh

I’m beyond irritated and annoying! I came here at 9:00 hungry after work. When i went in there it was no hello, politeness or anything. It was two people working and when i walked in a spanish girl that looked in her 20’s was sweeping. I was standing at the counter waiting for over 7 minutes because whoever was in the back never came out. Then the girl sweeping has the nerve to come over about to make my sandwich. I then ask her “Can she wash her hands” she goes to the sink do not use soap and just rubbed her hands under the water for 5 SECONDS. Then when i go to tell her I want white bread she says they only have WHEAT! They’re nasty, trifling, never have all the ingredients and never polite! Hire new staff please i will never be returning! I bet they dont even wash they hands before they make the sandwiches or make sure its sanitary. This the third tome i came and they was rude and just trifling letting other ingredients mix with eachother.. i wont be returning and this is my neighborhood subway.

The two workers on the front line seemed to be having a bad day I guess. Attitudes was very unpleasant, executing my order seemed irritating to him, and there was sarcasm. I would never refer friends or family to this particular location 🤔🙄💔

Horrible Customer Service I Arrived To Purchase Lunch Before Going Into Work @ 10:00AM And Was Told I Needed To Wait Another 20mins Because The Store Was Being Opened Late Due To The Employee In Walmart Shopping Instead Of Opening The Store During Business Hours.
Then Whoever This Employee Is Proceeded To Argue With Me About Her Being Late
So I’m Suppose To Wait Until She Put Her Grocery’s Up

This is the worst subway I have ever been. Such a poor service. Their behavior is extremely rude. There was a lady, age between 30-35, was extremely rude. Even she used racial slur against me. If u want respect, this place is not for u!!!!
People be tripping, don’t mind these 1 star reviews. It’s a mf subway, they need to lower some expectations

My go-to Five Guys in my area. Store is always clean, and the people there hustle to make your food. Of course, if you know anything about Five Guys, you already know they make the best burgers in their category.

I mean what can I say it's 5 guys it's the best burgers I ever had they are expensive but you get what you pay for I only go here but so often because of the  greasy foods but when I do I treat myself And their drink machine is the best out here for mixing flavors like vanilla Coke or vanilla Orange hi-ci, What would make this place even better if they had more parking nearby

Come with an appetite because they overload you with fries. Got a regular size fry and it came with a cup that it filled half the bag. It was so much, that u poured some out the bag and took the rest home. The burger was very tasty and full of flavor. You can build your own burger and it’s unlimited toppings. Free refills for the fountain drink, and you can dine in. There’s also free peanuts that you can request. I took that home with my remaining fries.

The only reason I didn’t give this at five is because the fries were overloaded with salt. When I picked up a fry, my fingers were covered and salt was falling from the fries.

Overall though, I recommend this place and their burgers. The service was good and made all my request happened. I’d come here again. 🤗
Very good burger place, generous with fries and toppings, just be careful not to order too much and swamp your burger

Parking is tricky, I used the parking lot adjacent to Five Guys (Eco Cleaners lot). I crossed the street to be greeted with a travel well spent. This place is clean and has friendly staff and the food smells great!

There is a scam on this gas station
I bough regular fuel but when I saw the recipt I saw i was charged V-Power fuel.
I did make sure i bump regular.
Listed on Shell’s website as a place to redeem fuel discount points, but in-person isn’t a participating location

Every time I come to this gas station I buy the same thing for $2.50 , this gas station tries to overcharge by $1 when the wrapping says $2 . I wouldn’t recommend going to this gas station for anything.
This station does have diesel even though the website states it doesn’t
Quite possibly the worst gas station in DMV avoid at all costs

ABSOLUTELY AMAZING. Fresh, delicious food and very friendly service. Table for two, we ordered the fried spinach, neck bones and beans, and a four piece fried chicken with mashed potatoes and Mac and cheese. Add corn bread! The chicken and the spinach were OFF THE CHART. You gotta try this place.

Listen to me! .......Please...if you are looking for hot, fresh, well seasoned food, decent portion sizes, attentive and polite staff and great atmosphere, then you must go to the Hitching Post. You will not be disappointed.
My mom, daughter and I were in DC for the day, we wanted some good soul food...and our expectations were exceeded to the umpth degree,
The catfish was delicious (in my Tommy Davidson -Martin show voice). Nothing was over seasoned or too salty, the fish was fried to perfection, mac and cheese was flavorful and rich, the greens were succulent. We cleaned our plates!
My only criticism would be, if I can even truly call it that is, they do not have yams on the menu. In my humble opinion, yams are the quintessential component of soul food. Please add yams to the menu!
Anytime I'm back in DC, this will be my spot!

My family went to the Hitching Post last week for the 1st time for a celebration dinner and we are really impressed with the restaurant!  The meals were all fresh, tasty and the service was great!   It had a cool vibe and comfortable inside seating.  The hostess was very welcoming, our waiter was very personable and knowledgable, we are looking forward to coming back!
Nice little cozy spot. Wait staff/mgr are very friendly. Ribs were delicious "fall off the bone".The calamari tasty and crunchy, not rubbery. Crabcakes were ok...l like more "lump".

NOT BLACK OWNED!!!!!
Very quaint and welcoming home that was converted to a restaurant. Indoor and outdoor setting makes it a plus. Location seems to be hidden by some trees and it was passed up several times. Very little parking. Food truly is less than delicious or even good at best. From kitchen to table time was not long, food just lacked flavor. The customer service is superb! Server SAUVE was extremely pleasant and informative with the menu options. Best part of this visit was the customer service and over all atmosphere.

We want to hear for a friend's birthday and I would have to give the food of score of just being okay. The waffles that I had didn't really have much flavor to it the amount of syrup they gave me was so little that the waffles just sucked it up and they were still dry. The chicken really didn't have too much flavor to it either all in all we did have a good time there with friends and the bottomless drinks is definitely a plus.

Holy heck what a cool spot. Great jukebox, really great vegetarian options, superb beer list. Went with a group and got to try the fried pickles, onion rings, the vegan wings, and the house veggie burger. Everything was incredible. My dining partners got to try the regular wings and burgers, and everyone really enjoyed their meals. Will definitely drop in again!

Tasty burgers, great services and a cute tucked away location. I got the "I'll have what she's having" which was perfectly cooked with brusselsprouts. My friends also loved their burgers and the blood orange cider was yum

First off just want to start with I work in this industry so as far as customer service goes they were 5 star. I’m only leaving a review because I feel like I paid $30 for a burger that I had to take the bottom bun off cause it was soaked in grease. Then the wings only 2 out of 4 had the Cajun seasoning on them. The waffle fries didn’t even have so much as salt on them. I think they have the potential to be really good if maybe the cook put a little more love into the plates. Just saying it overall was not worth the price.

Best rock and roll bar in the region. Excellent beer selection, all the food is excellent, and the cocktails are inspired, not pretentious. Highly recommend slash nuggs and the Barstool Rodeo.

In one of the bathrooms there's a poster of Debbie Harry that maintains eye contact with you the whole time. Feels very cozy.
I was surprised to know they served pig feet and chitterlings for you pork lovers. The serving was large. Great selection
They were out of all the popular items.  Get there at the beginning of the lunch hour or you will be short.

Terrible food. asked them to make my Orange chicken extra crispy. it was more soggy than any Orange chicken I've ever had. ill have to remember the Chinese food spot on Hawaii is not good. note to self.
Ordered the combination lo mein which is supposed to have chicken, pork, and shrimp. My bland lo mein had zero shrimp in it and the hot and sour soup was a tofu tasteless mess.

My Chicken and Cheese sub was horrible. Salty entirely to much mayonnaise the sandwich was warm,
& the cheese wasn't melted.  I ordered a ice tea after I asked if they had homemade tea I received instant tea & lemonade mixed.  I was told that was all they sell.
The  service was not good.
I Will NOT GO THERE AGAIN!!!

Pretty good carry out. Really quick. A little cluttered looking on the inside. Not pleasing to the eye on the outside as far as appearance. Good good tho. There is a $10 card minimum for those of you who are card users. They do have an atm inside for convenience.

"BEWARE" I Ordered General Tso's Chicken and Singapore noodles. The food was horrible!! Both meals appeared to be heated up frozen meals from the local Grocery Store Frozen Food Section! The Meals were definitely not freshly cooked with the onions, celery, carrots, etc. that normally comes when traditionally prepared!!

This place has been a great staple. Survived the gentrification and COVID. I hope they continue to stand and do well. The food is superb. I have not had a bad experience from here ever out of the 4 years I left the DMV, i came back and this place never changed. It's nostalgia for those of us who grew up here.

An update - 2023
They've been burning the shrimp egg foo yung  a lot lately. So I wouldn't recommend getting that dish anymore. It used to be the best in the area and I always try to tip. But they went as far as to telling me they were out of the dish because i asked them not to burn it this time. The food has become subpar with some dishes. I hope they can get back to what they used to be. It was the place I sent many of people to go. I'll update again in a few weeks.
Food was ok to good, not memorable. $40 for 2 combination plates and 10 wings is really over priced for cheap food.
I have been going here for more than 13yrs and love their food.

The crabs were okay I paid $60 for large males a few were big and light and they did not taste good at all. I know crab are not in season but I don't know where they got those crabs from they had a lot of black spots on them.
Crabs are the best and most reasonable around right now. Because you care about my pockets, I will care about yours and come often! Thank you for the delicious crabs everytime!

Food was good! The crabs had A LOT of seasoning!
Lol, I guess folks like it that way... I didn't need that much. It would be nice if they asked their customers if they want a lot or just enough seasoning to coat the crabs.

The shrimp that we ordered tasted like it didn't have any seasoning 😩. The seasoning from the crabs could have been shared with the shrimp (That's how much seasoning was on there!)- Whew!

July 22, 2022 purchased pound of shrimp then returned home an hour away. Proceeded to eat shrimp and found first one soft and mushy. Opened second shrimp was soft as it if not cooked completely. Went through several more to find same condition. Tried to call number on website and it’s just a recording and no other options to speak personally.
This is totally unexceptionable from any food establishments and it was to far to drive back to return under cooked or spoiled shrimp.
Food cost too much throw it away because of quality issues unable to consume. Totally disappointed and feel very upset of experience that occurred. Needless to say I will not spend or frequent this place again ever in future. Please beware of ruff n ready shrimp quality which is very poor. Please beware please beware.
Best crabs in town!! Meaty, tasty, seasoned to perfection!!! And don't forget to grab some crab legs and shrimp!!! The cocktail sauce is Amazing!! Alexa play music by DC PABLO!!

I was excited to received my food. The lady who fixed my sandwich the way I liked it. She was also respectable. They guy was too just had a bad vibe about and I was right. Felt sick after I ate it but a few hours later or next day. That's the only reason for my 1 star.
Worst subway staff I’ve ever encountered. I most def will drive the extra 15 mins next time I want subway 9/13/22 1 pm horrible customer service/ rude af
They do too much and make it seem like if you don't order everything you can on any particular trip that they'll skimp you...I don't like that.

I only purchased a soda but the gentleman working was nice enough to let me use the restroom. The store was very clean ,he was very polite and the bathroom smelled decent. When I get a craving for subway this is the place I'm coming to. Its comforting knowing a place keeps things clean..helps food digest better.
Had a chance to eat fresh this location is always clean..

So at this MC Donalds They are suppose to open at 5:30. It's on my way to work. They are usually there but not ready to open until they are ready. Maybe because the area. Other then that it's good as any decent mc donalds. Just don't have at work by 6- 630 you'll be late.
These ladies work well under pressure. I stopped in and the restaurant was very busy Leslie held it down!  They are always friendly.

It's decent. Fast service.  But if you are not Hispanic or white they'll someyimes do disrespect things like walk off on you when you get to the register after you have been waiting in line. Prices are slightly higher than other local McD's. Dining room is warn. With that said though,  they cook the food quickly and thoroughly and they make their fries correctly. The dining room though worn- this location is one of the list to have not been renovated with the new look- they keep the restaurant clean and the people of the neighborhood usually don't make trouble here.

I ordered breakfast through Uber Eats it did not take long however, My orange Juice spilled in my bag and Ieft a trail of it from the front door all the way back to my office. Please do a better job at properly packing food for delivery. I cant eat anything because of the spill. Terribly disappointed and starving!

I was surprised there was no drive thru there, but, hey, I got to stretch my legs and walk in to place my order.  A woman there was a former McDonald's employee took the time to help me download the McDonald's app. for my order - saved me lots of money on that order.  There's still good people in the world! ❤❤❤❤

I must say, even getting in the neighborhood of this Chik Fil A, I had an impression that this would not be my favorite at all because it was all trashy and very shady(I mean the neighborhood). So I had a reward of free spicy sandwich on my phone and tried to redeem it but did not work. So I just paid for it with cash.The spicy chicken that they served me was so plain, even with pickles. Check out the image. However I went to a different location in Washington DC area(by Tenley Public Library) and their spicy chicken sandwich had an option of cheese(if wanted it), tomatoes and lettuce. I attached the picture as well to compare the differences in the supposedly same sandwich. I do not recommend this location to anyone that expects all the food from Chik Fil A to be similar in one way or the other (same ingredients) and wants to enjoy because I believe they can do way better than that by making sure all their restaurants serve similar items on the menus everywhere rather than distinctive items.

Note: 1st picture from this location reviewed(so plain) and the 2nd one from the other location by Tenley Public Library(loaded). Yet cost the same price.

So upon completing my late night shopping at the Walmart that was near to this Chick Fil A location, I decided to get Chicken Nuggets to snack on the walk home. However upon approaching the door, it was locked and the sign on the door stated open 6a-10p. But what really made my BLOOD BOIL when the staff shewed me away like I was a fly, and laughed at me. After that, when I asked for the Store Manager, they stated that there was sign on the door that states that the Dine In area closes at 9p, and it was clearly where Guest cannot see it. Yet the Managers and Staff still laughed at me, causing me to become more and more angry. I never experienced this at any Chick Fil A, and they need to hire ADULTS instead of these SNOT NOSE A** KIDS! #GHETTOCHICKFILA

This is the best Chick-fil-A in the DMV my food is always made with good quality, the staff is very nice, My food never takes very long to come out I've been coming here for the past 3 years and never had a problem

I am a non meat eater. So, all I usually get is breakfast. I do love the kale salad, but it is too small.
I have had some issues with not receiving the correct breakfast. I will get to work and discover it is incorrect.
So, make sure you check your food. It has happened to me 3 different times. I have mentioned it, and they apologize, and keep going.
I gave them a 4 because when you get your food, it is hot, and the young ladies at the drive-through in the morning are great!!

The food is good but the need to rethink traffic flow. You can barely get in to the drive through without blocking its exit for people who got their food, only to get stuck after you got your and are trying to leave.
The staff was young but courteous and friendly. So missed a star for the cars pile up each time during peak hours.
Food is Delicious..I love Coming here for lunch!! Fish subs Great, baked chicken wing platter Bomb! Most food is Very Satisfying..
Great place for good food on your lunch break if you are in the area

Breakfast off the chain
Country sausage is excellent
Thick Country bacon is everyone's favorite

It was my first time here. The people that work there was very nice. The food on the other was not good. I got a catfish dinner and a crab cake. The catfish was too salty and too soft. The greens had no taste and they were very soft also. The crab cake had no taste. I spent almost $30 for food that I don’t enjoy at all. I had the hardest time trying to eat the catfish because of how salty it was.

Been a customer for a decade now. Excellent soul food, stopped selling chittlins due to pandemic and recently started serving hogmolls(sic). Either way, the food is good, healthy portions, slightly pricey-but worth it.
The burgers were cooked well while not being overcooked. The season fries are the way but if you need to dip them then go with the standard fries. The shakes are very good.

WHAT A WASTE OF MONEY AND TIME! Ticket #215  1/11/23. I paid over $14.00 for a chicken sandwich and onions rings. Chicken sandwich was horrible! No seasoning, bland taste. Onion rings were huge and greasy. Very disappointing! I guess they're famous for beef burgers and smoothies because this chicken sandwich and onion rings SUCKS!
Small area, burgers are okay, steak N cheese is light on the steak but tasty. Shakes are pricey but good. Staff looses focus sometimes and orders come out late.

Food was good, but when I stepped inside to pick up my order the smell of cleaning products was unbelievably strong. To the point where I was concerned about whether or not it was even healthy. Wouldn’t order from this location again just because of that. I’m no scientist but I kept thinking about the toxins from the cleaning products contaminating my food… not even sure if that’s possible but that’s how strong the smell was. Food and customer service were good though…
They advertise that they are the best burger in Washington DC, and I have to say, it was pretty darn good. And the onion rings are, indeed, the best onion rings I've ever had.
Good environment and friendly staff. The burger is amazing overall everything is good.
I wish they had a selection of local beers or something, would be 100% our go-to shop to pick up quick items if they had wine or beer.
Friendly staff and good selection.  Also a Z-burger is coming there soon!
Nice and clean inside. Friendly staff
Good burger...

I’m so glad this place has finally opened! The food was out of this world, well-priced and super fresh! The staff is incredibly friendly and the vibe is great. Highly recommend for takeout or a nice dinner in their gorgeous little restaurant.
Really flavorful pupusas and attentive staff.  We ordered for takeaway and it was hot and well wrapped.

MAMÁ CHEPA IS A PLACE WHERE YOU CAN ENJOY GOOD QUALITY AND GOOD TASTE LATIN FOOD EVERYTHING IS FRESH AND TASTY.  ON THIS OCCASION I HAD THE PLEASURE OF TRYING A DISH CALLED GORDITO PLATTE. IN MY OPINION, IT HAS A VERY GOOD TASTE AND BEAUTIFUL PRESENTATION OF ITS DISHES.  WITHOUT A DOUBT IT IS A PLACE THAT I WOULD ALWAYS VISIT FOR ITS FOOD AND GOOD ATMOSPHERE AND ATTENTIVE STAFF
Amazing customer service, affordable and the food doesn’t take too long, we had our foods really fast

100% recommend! Seriously delicious pupusas, and their sauce was some of the best I’ve ever had! As a bonus, it’s very affordably priced. We dined inside, and the inside is really nice and the staff were super friendly. We’ll definitely be back!

Fun neighborhood bar for trivia and just catching up with friends. Or shenanigans. The chicken tenders with fries are incredible. The dice roll combo is always a fun surprise. Definitely a way to elevate the night. Staff are chill. Feel a bit like a regular when I go. Check their Instagram and or site for details about trivia.
The best cruchwrap in town!! It was so good!! 🤩🤩 thanks Stephanie for showing us this cool place!

The BEST bar in DC. We stumbled onto Jackie Lees when we moved to the neighborhood and I can’t believe I ever lived without it.

The food is great - BBQ and “vegan junk food” vibes, and the drink selection is top. Bartenders / owners / friends - you cannot beat them.

It’s the type of place I would go to alone just to hang out, or bring out of town friends to. Somehow, it also manages to be “parent friendly” where my boomer parents feel right at home, too.

Lots of familiar faces every time we go - so I know I’m not alone in my opinions.

Be nice. Tip well. Come back often.

Great bar! Makes me miss DC! An actual in the neighborhood hang spot! Awesome beer, great ambiance, good prices, friendly staff and an amazing VEGETARIAN Bánh Mi w/ collard greens front and center!!! Just go and enjoy 👌
Such fun at this bar for a staff party. Attentive staff, great cocktails, and a fun, chill vibe. Wish I lived closer!

So the place is a classic carry out.... "hurry up and buy" type of atmosphere. But the food is worth every penny. You can customize your order the way you like and it comes out piping hot! And the egg rolls are not only deliciously amazing, but HUGE!! I have NEVER seen egg rolls so big. You can eat them as a meal by themselves. I love this place. Just wish they would have a better customer service like attitude 🤷🏾‍♀️

In the past five years, Twin Dragon has always been on point, with fresh ingredients with developed flavor, while ready in about 15 minutes. When you think about it, most restaurants, period, can't do that. For what is worth, sweet and sour chicken, crispy beef (like Gen Tao's, but thinner strips), and hot and sour soup are wins. Should have a 4.4 rating at least. (perhaps if they did a little remodel).

Lived a few blocks away from TD back in the 60s and 70s.  Went to high school with the Lee family kids.  TDs egg rolls were to die for.  I had a supervisor who lived in Silver Springs and bought her egg rolls on the way home.  Given the few unfavorable reviews here, I want to revisit TD soon and decide for myself. I pray the egg rolls are the same.  Their pork foo young was delicious, as well.  My parents loved the pepper steak. I loved this place; hope I can say this again.  Gave a one star until I revisit and decide.  Hopefully, I can raise to a five star.

Ordered 10 egg rolls 8 shrimp & 2 pork. The breading was Very tough/dry hard to bite into and the pork was very dark, dry and tasted old. Cabbage very very over cooked. Called the Restaurant to notify them and the lady screamed the entire time talking to me and to a guy in the back in her language (I guess repeating what I was saying) and asked me what do I want her to do about it? She said you ordered 10 and someone else ordered 100 and they had no problem. I asked her what did that have to do with my order? She then began to speak very fast and loud and then hung up the phone. I called back twice and no answer the 3rd time a guy answered and I asked him if I was hung up on and each time he said what do you need, what do you want? I will NEVER patronize this place again!! Bad customer service and old food I won’t do! If I didn’t live in MD - I would’ve returned the dry/hard egg-rolls. Don’t waste your time and money. I should’ve read the other review about dryness before ordering. But lesson learned!! They are not worth a picture

Pretty good for a carry out place. Their portions are huge.  The shrimp rolls were really good, and their chicken wings and fries are not greasy at all. The location is a bit sketchy, but they get you in-and-out pretty quickly
